<paragraph blockId="6.[160,1156,419,1138]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,268,419,445]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thorne G &amp; Swanger HH" box="[285,593,420,445]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" pagination="223" refId="ref19695" refString="Thorne G, Swanger HH. 1936. A monograph of the nematode genera Dorylaimus Dujardin, Aporcelaimus n. g., Dorylaimoides n. g., and Pungentus n. g. Cap Zoologica. 6: 223." type="journal article" year="1936">Thorne and Swanger (1936)</bibRefCitation>
proposed the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorne and Swanger" authorityYear="1936" box="[829,984,420,445]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[829,984,420,445]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Dorylaimoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorne and Swanger" authorityYear="1936" box="[1046,1126,420,445]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="teres">
<emphasis box="[1046,1126,420,445]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">D. teres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as its 
<typeStatus box="[200,251,455,480]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">type</typeStatus>
species from the 
<collectingCountry box="[479,530,455,480]" name="United States of America" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">USA</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Altherr E" box="[545,710,455,480]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" pagination="429 - 460" refId="ref18016" refString="Altherr E. 1953. Nematodes du sol du Jura vaudois et franchais. I Bul Soc Vaud Sc Nat. 65 (284): 429 - 460." type="journal article" year="1953">Altherr (1953)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Thorne G" box="[779,946,455,480]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref19654" refString="Thorne G. 1974. Nematodes of the Northern Great plains. Part II. Dorylaimoidea in part (Nemata: Adenophorea). Tech Bull Agric Exp Station, South Dakota State Univ. 41: 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="1974">Thorne (1974)</bibRefCitation>
reported it from 
<collectingCountry box="[160,290,489,514]" name="Switzerland" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
and the 
<collectingCountry box="[397,447,489,514]" name="United States of America" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">USA</collectingCountry>
, respectively. 
<bibRefCitation author="Goseco CG &amp; Ferris VR &amp; Ferris JM" box="[605,964,489,514]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" refId="ref18466" refString="Goseco CG, Ferris VR, Ferris JM. 1976. Revision in Leptonchoidea (Nematoda: Dorylaimida). Dorylaimoides in Dorylaimoididae, Dorylaimoididinae, Calolaimus and Timmus n. gen. in Dorylaimoididae, Calolaiminae, and Miranema in Mirannematidae. Res. Bull., Agric. Expt. Sta., Purdue Univ., West Lafayette No. 941; p. 46." type="journal volume" year="1976">Goseco, Ferris and Ferris (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, in their revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorne and Swanger" authorityYear="1936" box="[310,465,524,549]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[310,465,524,549]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Dorylaimoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, made a detailed study of the 
<typeStatus box="[810,860,524,549]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">type</typeStatus>
population as well as two other populations from the 
<collectingCountry box="[483,530,559,584]" name="United States of America" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[545,640,559,584]" country="United States of America" name="Missouri" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Missouri</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[702,791,559,584]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Arizona</collectingRegion>
). They (1976) differentiated this species from 
<taxonomicName authority="Jairajpuri, 1965" authorityName="Jairajpuri" authorityYear="1965" box="[319,617,593,618]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="indicus">
<emphasis box="[319,430,593,618]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">D. indicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jairajpuri MS" box="[442,617,593,618]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" pagination="124 - 125" refId="ref18902" refString="Jairajpuri MS. 1965. Dorylaimoides indicus n. sp. (Nematode: Dorylaimoidea) from India. Lab J Sci Tech. 3: 124 - 125." type="journal article" year="1965">Jairajpuri, 1965</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of a more conoid tail, from 
<taxonomicName authority="Siddiqi, 1964" authorityName="Siddiqi" authorityYear="1964" box="[160,447,628,653]" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="parateres">
<emphasis box="[160,292,628,653]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">D. parateres</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Siddiqi MR" box="[301,447,628,653]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" pagination="626 - 634" refId="ref19460" refString="Siddiqi MR. 1964. Three new species of Dorylaimoides Thorne &amp; Swanger, 1936, with descriptions of Xiphinema orbum n. sp. (Nematoda: Dorylaimoidea). Nematologica. 9 (4): 626 - 634. doi: 10.1163 / 187529263 X 00737." type="journal article" year="1964">Siddiqi, 1964</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by having a longer pharyngeal bulb, and from 
<taxonomicName authority="Heyns, 1963" authorityName="Heyns" authorityYear="1963" class="Adenophorea" family="Leptonchidae" genus="Dorylaimoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dorylaimida" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="thecolaimus">
<emphasis box="[992,1156,628,653]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">D. thecolaimus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Heyns J" box="[160,300,663,688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" pagination="7 - 15" refId="ref18535" refString="Heyns J. 1963. Five new species of Leptonchidae (Nematoda: Dorylaimoidea) from South Africa. Pro Helminth Soc Wash. 30: 7 - 15." type="journal article" year="1963">Heyns, 1963</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by a more anterior vulva position. Peralta and Peña-Santiago (1995) also redescribed this species, with four different populations from 
<collectingCountry box="[859,924,697,722]" name="Spain" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Spain</collectingCountry>
. The morphometrics of the present population conforms well with the 
<typeStatus box="[761,811,732,757]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">type</typeStatus>
population except in having a longer ventral arm of the odontostyle (7.5–8.5 vs 6 μm) and a slightly longer tail (29– 32 vs 21–29 μm). The present population conforms well with 
<bibRefCitation author="Altherr E" box="[854,1025,801,826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" pagination="429 - 460" refId="ref18016" refString="Altherr E. 1953. Nematodes du sol du Jura vaudois et franchais. I Bul Soc Vaud Sc Nat. 65 (284): 429 - 460." type="journal article" year="1953">Altherr’s (1953)</bibRefCitation>
population but slightly differs from 
<bibRefCitation author="Thorne G" box="[427,600,836,861]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref19654" refString="Thorne G. 1974. Nematodes of the Northern Great plains. Part II. Dorylaimoidea in part (Nemata: Adenophorea). Tech Bull Agric Exp Station, South Dakota State Univ. 41: 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="1974">Thorne’s (1974)</bibRefCitation>
population in having higher b (6.9–7.8 vs 5.6–5.9) and c (47–55 vs 31–43) ratios. The present specimens also conform well with Goseco et al.’s (1976) specimens; however, they slightly differ from the Spanish population described by Peralta and Peña-Santiago (1995) in having a long and slender body (L = 1.5–1.6 vs 
<quantity box="[331,466,975,1000]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.1">1.1–1.4 mm</quantity>
, a = 39–43 vs 29–39) and differently shaped tail (rounded to convex-conoid, its terminal part not dorsally bent, vs rounded to convex-conoid, sometimes terminal part bent dorsally). These slight variations should be considered intraspecific as well as geographical variability. This species is reported here for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[221,279,1113,1138]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
